# Git — Commit Author

When creating a git commit, always use this identity:

- **Name:** Iman Suherman
- **Email:** iman.suherman@gmail.com

## Agent workflow

Pass name and email on the commit command without changing git config:

```bash
git -c user.name="Iman Suherman" -c user.email="iman.suherman@gmail.com" commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Commit message here.

EOF
)"
```

Apply the same `-c user.name=... -c user.email=...` flags for commits in every repo.

## Safety

- Never run `git config` to set user.name or user.email.
- Do not use a different author unless the user explicitly requests it.
